data.text:
STREET CLOSURE ALERT: Because of the St. Patricks Day Parade, there are multiple street closures in downtown Aurora on Sunday, March 17. Beginning at 8 a.m., Downer Avenue will be closed between Broadway/25 and River Street. From 9:45 a.m.-Noon Benton from Broadway to Stolp will be closed. From 10:30 a.m.-Noon Stolp from Benton to Galena will be closed. Please know the parking Garage on Stolp & Downer will be mostly inaccessible from 10:30 a.m.-Noon with the street closures. Downer from Stolp to Broadway/25 will re-open at approximately 1 p.m. Valet for the 1 p.m. matinee will line-up on Galena, in the far right lane next to Altiro. Please do not pull directly up in front of Paramount for Valet Service. If Stolp opens early, please do not line-up there either. Vehicles will only be accepted on Galena, next to Altiro Restaurant on the corner of Stolp & Galena. The City is anticipating large crowds, so please give yourself plenty of time to locate parking and get to the theater.

Nominated for 15 Tony Awards with 10 Wins, including Best Musical!

The music of Elton John brings to life the story of Billy Elliot, an 11-year-old English boy who stumbles upon a ballet class during his weekly boxing lesson. His surprise love for dance must be hidden at all costs, especially from his coal miner father. With the help from his sharp-tongued teacher, Mrs. Wilkinson, Billy gets the chance to attend a prestigious ballet school and must decide what is most important: doing what he loves or doing what other people want. Billy Elliot is a coming-of-age story that inspires us all to do what you love no matter what other people think. BE TRUE TO YOU.

Book and Lyrics by LEE HALL

Music by ELTON JOHN

Originally Directed by STEPHEN DALDRY

Orchestrations by MARTIN KOCH

Executive Producers [Original Production] ANGELA MORRISON and DAVID FURNISH

Producers [Original Production] TIM BEVAN, ERIC FELLNER, JON FINN, SALLY GREENE

Originally presented in London by Universal Pictures Stage Productions, Working Title Films and Old

Vic Productions in association with Tiger Aspect. Based on the Universal Pictures/Studio Canal Film.

BILLY ELLIOT: THE MUSICAL is presented through special arrangement with Music Theatre International [MTI]. All authorized performance materials are also supplied by MTI. www.mtishows.com

SIGN INTERPRETED PERFORMANCES

There will be two certified sign interpreters translating all dialogue and lyrics into American Sign Language at the following performances:

2023-24 Broadway Season  Use code: ASLPARAMOUNT

Billy Elliot  March 22, 2024 at 8 p.m.

Beautiful: The Carole King Musical  June 7, 2024 at 8 p.m.

2023-24 BOLD Season  Use code: ASLBOLD

A Streetcar Named Desire  April 19, 2024 at 8 p.m.

You must enter promo code to unlock ASL Interpreted section and special $30 price.

OPEN CAPTIONED PERFORMANCES

Anyone who is looking to purchase tickets to this performance may do so either online, over the phone or in person. There is no special pricing for this performance. Performances for each show include:

Billy Elliot: Thursday, March 21 at 7 p.m.

Beautiful: The Carole King Musical: Wednesday, June 12 at 1:30 p.m.

Learn more about ASL and open captioned performances.

Paramount Theatre is happy to be part of the 2024 Chicago Theatre Week and offer $30 tickets for select performances to Billy Elliot: The Musical during Feb. 8  18 (Zone D). Use code CTW24 to redeem your offer. Buy Tickets Here!

*Discount applicable only for select February 8-18 performances of Billy Elliot: The Musical. Limit 4 tickets per customer in Zone D. Not valid toward previous purchases. All sales final. No refunds or exchanges. Offer available online only, while supplies last. Expires 2/18/2024.
